[Nouns] compromise, commutation, composition; middle term, mezzo termine; compensation [more]; abatement of differences, adjustment, mutal concession.
[Verbs] compromise, commute, compound; take the mean; split the difference, meet one halfway, give and take; come to terms (contract) [more]; submit to arbitration, abide by arbitration; patch up, bridge over, arrange; straighten out, adjust, differences, agree; make the best of, make a virtue of necessity; take the will for the deed.
